25|$|On November 2, 1918, the State Council {{adopted a}} <b>constitutional</b> <b>act.</b> At the time, {{it was still}} {{constrained}} by the decision of July 11, 1918, declaring Lithuania a constitutional monarchy, {{with close ties to}} Germany. In a changing environment, the council chose to adopt the <b>constitutional</b> <b>act</b> without specifying the form of government or the head of state, leaving the decisions to the Constituent Assembly (Steigiamasis Seimas).|$|E
