50|$|After {{the fall}} of the junta and the return to {{civilian}} rule under Konstantinos Karamanlis in August 1974, the legal and <b>constitutional</b> <b>acts</b> of the military regime were deemed invalid, and a new referendum was held on 8 December 1974, which confirmed the abolishment of the monarchy. In the interim, Gizikis, remained in office as President. After the plebiscite, he was succeeded by the first elected President, Michail Stasinopoulos.|$|R
